## Decision checklist

**New work**

- [ ] Searched for existing implementation
- [ ] Reuse is 100% scenario-aligned, or duplication is intentional
- [ ] Shared code lives in the right repo/layer; dependencies are clean
- [ ] If change could break released production consumers: phased plan + post-deploy ledger entry (see §5)

**Fix**

- [ ] Root cause identified; diff is as small as possible
- [ ] Grep’d consumers; chose direct rename/canonical import over alias/re-export shim when blast radius is small
- [ ] Chose refactor only when patch stack or clarity warrants it
- [ ] Any deletion/simplification keeps compatibility and future support

**Frontend render bug (if applicable)**

- [ ] ≤2 code-only attempts before log-assisted diagnosis (or developer asked for logs earlier)
- [ ] Diagnostic logs are minimal, prefixed, and copy-friendly
- [ ] All Phase B logs removed after the fix lands
